parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high pressure AC line can cause the refrigerant oil to spray onto the serpentine belt, leading to improper acceleration and potential accidents.
symptoms: refrigerant oil sprayed on the serpentine belt

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shifter assembly can cause the vehicle to become stuck in park, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Unable to shift vehicle from park
requiring the use of a blunt object to insert into the shift lock relay to shift out of park.

and unnerving sounds during transmission operation.
